Description: On your stomach, place the roller on the inside of your thigh. Slowly roll the inner thigh to find a tender spot. Hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on the other side.
Place roller under the mid-calf. Cross the opposite leg over the top of the other. Slowly roll calf to find a tender spot. Hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on the other side.
Place the foam roller under your hamstring, just before the glute. Roll your hamstring area to find a tender spot. Hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on the other side.

Lie on one side with the foam roller just in front of the hip. Cross the top leg over the lower leg, placing that foot on the floor. Slowly roll from the hip joint down toward the knee to find the tender spot. Hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

Stand with one leg in front of the other, with the front leg slightly bent. Point the toes of your back foot inward. Raise the arm that is on the same side as your back leg and shift your body forward, reaching over your head until a stretch is felt in front of your pelvis. Hold the side stretch and then rotate backwards. Hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

Stand about three feet from a wall and put one foot behind you ensuring your toes are facing forward. Keep your heel on the ground and lean forward with your back knee straight. Hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.
Begin in a wide-leg stance with toes pointing straight. Bend one leg and shift the hips toward that side. Hold for 30 seconds. Return to the starting position and repeat on the other side.

Begin on your back with your legs on the floor. Bring one knee towards your chest and slowly straighten your leg so your toes point up. Keep a firm hold on the back of your leg as your pull it toward you to deepen the stretch. Breathe deeply and hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on opposite side.

Begin on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, shoulder-width apart. Squeeze your glutes and lift your hips off the floor to a flat-back position. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then relax and bring your hips back to the ground. Repeat for recommended reps.

Begin on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on the floor, shoulder-width apart. Lift and extend one foot in the air. Contract your glutes and lift your hips off the floor to a flat-back position, lift  Hold for 1-2 seconds and then relax, bringing your hips back to the ground but keeping your leg in the air. Repeat for recommended reps. Switch sides and repeat.

Display Name: Hip Bridge on Unstable Surface - Double Leg
Exercise: Hip Bridge (double leg) on unstable surface
Description: Begin on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on a pillow, shoulder-width apart. Contract your abdomen, allowing your lower back to be flush with the ground. Squeeze your glutes and lift your hips off the floor to a flat-back position. Hold for 1-2 seconds, then relax and bring your hips back to the ground. Repeat for recommended reps.

Display Name: Hip Bridge on Unstable Surface - Single Leg
Exercise: Hip Bridge (single leg) on unstable surface
Description: Begin on your back with your knees bent and your feet flat on a pillow, shoulder-width apart. Lift and extend one foot in the air. Contract your glutes and lift your hips off the floor to a flat-back position, lift and hold for 1-2 seconds and then relax, bringing your hips back to the ground but keeping your leg in the air. Repeat for recommended reps. Switch sides and repeat.

Display Name: Single Leg Balance Reach - Multiple Directions
Description: Stand with your hands on your hips and feet shoulder-width a part. Engage your core and glutes as you take one leg and reach forward, tapping your foot on the ground in front of you. Move back to the starting position. Next, reach out to the side with the same leg, maintaining the alignment of your other knee and continuing to engage your core and glutes. Move back to the starting position. Finish by reaching behind your body with the same leg. Repeat for the recommended reps, switch sides and repeat.

Stand with your feet shoulder width apart and toes pointing forward and arms over your head. Bend your knees and sit back with your hips as if into a chair. As you squat, maintain balance by looking forward and keeping your chest up. Straighten up once maximum depth is reached. Repeat for recommended reps.

Begin in a standing position with your toes pointing forward. Turn one foot to the outisde. With the opposite foot step forward into a lunge position, keeping your hips facing the front. Place your hands on your hips for balance. Hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

Begin on an elevated surface (i.e. stair/step) with heels hanging off. Lift one leg off the ground (place hands on nearby wall for support). Push onto toes of the other leg and hold for 1-2 seconds. Lower heel back down beyond level of surface to stretch the calf. Repeat with opposite leg.

Display Name: Lying Knee Flexion and Hip Internal Rotation
Exercise: Knee Flexion with Hip Internally Rotated
Description: Begin on your back with one knee bent and the other leg on the floor. Wrap a towel or band around your shin and grasp the ends. Turn your toes in and bring your knee in toward your midline. Pull to slide your foot as close to you as possible, maintaining the position of your knee. Hold for 2-3 seconds, then relax and let your foot slide back to starting position. Repeat for recommended number of reps then complete on the other side.

Sit with your buttocks on top of a foam roller. Cross one leg over the other so that the ankle is over the knee. Shift your weight to the same side as the crossed leg, rolling over the buttocks until you feel tension in your upper glute. You may assist the stretch by using one hand to pull the bent knee towards your chest. Holdfor 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

Begin on the floor with both knees bent, feet flat on the floor. Bring your ankle to the opposite knee to assume a "Figure-4" position. Pull the leg still on the ground to your chest until the stretch is felt through the upper hamstring and glute. Hold stretch for 30 seconds. Repeat with other leg.

Exercise: Resisted Hip Adduction and Internal Rotation

Description: Begin on your stomach with the foamroll beneath one thigh. Keeping that foot off of the ground, shift as much weight onto the leg to be stretched as is tolerable, roll the length of the muscle from the knee to the hip, holding points of tension for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

Begin in a lunge with your back knee and your front foot on the floor. Shift your weight forward, keeping your hips facing the front until you feel a stretch in your hip and hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.
column10: make sure front leg is  extended out a bit  more to emphasize stretch

Description: Begin on your hands and knees with your back flat. At the same time, raise the right arm and left leg until the extended arm and leg are horizontal. Pause briefly before lowering the arm and leg in the same path as the upward movement. Complete the assigned reps and repeat with the other side.

Begin on your stomach with your arms by your side and palms flat on the floor. Keeping your neck in a neutral position lift up your shoulders, pinching your shoulder blades together and chest off of the floor. Release back down to the floor. Repeat for recommended number of reps.
Begin with your foot resting on a towel, flat on the floor. Draw the towel towards you by scrunching your toes. Keep the heel in contact with the floor throughout. Switch sides and repeat.

Begin on your stomach and place a ball or roller beneath one hip. Keeping that foot off of the ground, shift as much weight onto the leg to be rolled as is tolerable, roll along the hip region, holding points of tension for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

Lie on one side with the arm closest to the ground over your head with thumb facing upwards. Place the foam roller under the arm. Slowly roll down your side back and forth to find the tender spot. Hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on other side.

Begin seated with legs extended in front of you. Cross one leg over the other and place that foot on the other side of the extended leg. Extend your arm and place your elbow on the outside of the bent knee. Place your other hand on the floor for support. Move into a twist and push your elbow into your knee to deepen the twist. Hold for 30 seconds, then repeat the stretch on the other side.

Kneel in front of a chair, ball, or foam roller and place one arm on top of the object with your thumb pointed up toward the ceiling. Keep the other hand on the ground. Lower your hips back toward your heels until a stretch is felt alongside the torso. Hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

Display Name: Ankle Stretch and Hold (Away From You)

Description: Stand with both feet on the edge of a step. The balls of your feet and toes should be the only parts of your foot on the platform. Lift your heels by pressing up through your toes and contracting your calf muscles. Slowly lower your heels to the neutral starting position.

Display Name: Double Leg (Up) - Single Leg (Down) Calf Raise
Exercise: Double Leg (up); Single leg (down) calf raise
Description: Begin on an elevated surface (ie. stair/step) with heels hanging off. Push onto toes with both legs, then lift one leg off the ground. With control, lower the other heel back down to the level of the surface. Repeat with opposite leg for recommended number of reps.

Lay on your side, supporting your weight on your forearm and on a foam roller placed on the outside of your lower leg. Your upper leg can either be on top of your lower leg, or you can cross it in front of you. Raise your hips off of the ground and begin to roll from below the knee to above the ankle on the side of your leg, pausing at points of tension. Repeat on the other leg.

Lie on your side on the ground with the roller underneath the outside of your lower leg. Hold yourself up by placing the same side forearm and opposite side hand on the ground. Roll back and forth over the outside portion of your lower leg. Hold tender areas for about 30 seconds or until discomfort decreases. To increase pressure, stack one leg on top of the other and roll the bottom leg.
Lie on your stomach and place roller on the inside portion of your shin. Slowly roll the inner shin to find a tender spot. Hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on the other side.

Start off standing (can be performed seated) with shoes off. Using a roller or a similar object, place your foot against the object across the arch of your foot. Press down firmly, rolling across the arch of your foot. Hold for 10-30 seconds, and then switch feet.

Stand with your feet shoulder width apart and weight balanced across your foot. Lift your toes upward toward your shins, keeping your heels on the ground. Hold briefly at the top, then slowly let your toes return to the ground. Repeat for assigned reps.

Stand in a shoulder-width stance with your toes flat on the edge of a box or step with your heels and mid-foot hanging off the edge so you feel a stretch in your calf. Use the wall or a rail as a support to stay balanced. Push your toes into the box so your heels raise up, pause, then lower yourself back to the starting position, being sure to feel a stretch in your calves.

Lie on your back with the knees bent and the soles of the feet on the floor. This is your neutral position. On an exhale, contract your abdomen to round your back so it is flush against the ground. Your hips should not leave the floor. Hold for 1-2 seconds, maintaining the abdominal contraction, then return to the neutral position. Repeat this movement for the recommended reps.

Display Name: Posterior Pelvic Tilt with Hip Bridge
Exercise: Posterior Pelvic Tilt with Hip Bridge
Description: Lie on your back with knees bent and feet flat on the floor. This is your neutral position. Contract your abdomen and round your back so it is flush with the ground. Maintaining the contraction, squeeze your glutes and bring your hips off the ground to a bridge position. Hold for 2-3 seconds, then bring your hips back down. Once your hips are on the floor, relax your abdomen to return back to the neutral position. Repeat this movement for the recommended number of reps.

Exercise: Bent Knee Hip External Rotation (On Side)
Description: Begin by lying on your side with your legs stacked and knees bent. Initiate the exercise by opening (abducting) the leg on top, pushing your knee away from your body. Maintain contact between your feet throughout the movement. Pause at the top of the motion, and then return to the starting position. Repeat for the desired number of reps. Switch sides and repeat.

Begin in a wide stance. Bend your knees so you are in a half-squat position. Keep your arms up in front of your to maintain balance. Engaging your core and glutes, step out with one leg and follow with the other, making sure your feet do not come closer than shoulder-width apart. Continue stepping out sideways for the recommended number of reps, maintaining the half-squat position. Rest, and repeat in the opposite direction.

Lie on your back with your legs straight and your arms overhead. Bend your hips and knees. Contract your abdomen so your low back is flush with the ground. Initiate the exercise by bringing one leg and the opposite arm to the ground, straightening the knee and hip to bring the leg just above the ground. Stay tight and return the working limbs to the starting position. Repeat on the opposite side, alternating until the set is complete.

Begin on your stomach and position your elbows beneath your shoulders. Lift your body off the ground from your forearms and knees. Hold your body straight by keeping your abdominal muscles and your thigh muscles tight. Squeeze your glutes for stability and don't let your hips drop. Try to keep a straight line from your head and neck to your back. Hold this position for 30 seconds.

Begin on your stomach and position your elbows underneath your shoulders. Lift your body off the ground so you are supported on your foreamrs and toes. Maintain alignment through contracting your core and squeezing through your glutes and thighs. Ensure your hips do not drop during this exercise. Hold for 30 seconds, then relax back to the floor.

Begin on your stomach and position your elbows underneath your shoulders. Lift your body off the ground so you are supported on your foreamrs and toes. Maintain alignment through contracting your core and squeezing through your glutes and thighs. From here, lift one leg up by squeezing through your glute--hold for 2 seconds then drop back down to the ground. Ensure your hips do not drop during this exercise. Repeat for recommended reps, then rest. Repeat on the other leg.

Display Name: Side Plank (Knees Bent) w/ Leg Lifts
Exercise: Side Plank Knees Bent Leg Lifts
Side Plank Knees Straight Leg Lifts

Description: Lie face down with your hands under your shoulders. Point your feet downwards to lengthen your spine. Slowly push your torso up as far as you comfortably can â€“ try to get your hips to rise off the floor slightly. Hold the stretch for 30 seconds and then lower down to starting position.

Exercise: Double leg squat with overhead press

Description: From a seated position, place a foam roll under your lower back. Cross your arms in front of you and protract your shoulders. Raise your hips off of the floor and lean back, keeping your weight on your lower back. Roll over your lower back, holding points of tension for 30 seconds. Repeat on the other side.

Begin on your hands and knees with your hands shoulder-width apart, and back flat (spine neutral). Keep your knees and ankles separated and the tops of your feet on the floor as you shift your weight back over your heels, lengthening your spine, relaxing your head and neck, and reaching forward through your fingertips. Breathe deeply and hold for 30 seconds.

Kneel on all fours, then place one hand on the opposite side of the other hand - reaching as far away from your body as possible in a diagonal pattern. Keep the hand in position as you sit your buttocks back toward your heels to increase the intensity of stretch. Hold for 30 seconds. Switch sides and repeat.

This exercise will be performed in 4 directions. First, point your toes down and press them into the top of your other foot. Hold for 1-2 seconds, relax, then repeat for recommended number of reps. Next, move your foot underneath your other foot, then pull up toward the top foot. Hold, then relax and repeat. Push your toes into the side of your other foot. Hold, relax and repeat. Cross your leg over the other and push the outside of your foot into your other foot. Hold, relax and repeat.

Stand with your legs shoulder width apart and hold onto a table or chair in front of you for support. Keep your knee straight and toes pointed, and kick your leg backward slowly activating your glute. Slowly return to the starting position. Complete assigned reps and switch sides. Next, assume the same starting position but kick your leg out laterally away from your body. Complete assigned reps and switch sides.

Exercise: Bent Knee Hip External Rotation (On Side)

Description: Sit on the floor with your back straight and legs extended and spread slightly apart. Begin with your toes pointed up, so the soles of your feet are flat. Point point one foot downward, as though pressing down on the gas pedal of a car, and hold for a count. Return to the starting position, as though letting up on the gas. This completes one repetition of the stretch. Complete assigned reps, switch sides, and repeat.

Stand tall with your legs straight and arms hanging at your sides. Kick one knee up, bringing it as high as comfortable. Grasp it with both hands and gently pull it up slightly higher, hugging it to the body. Slowly lower to repeat with the opposite side. Each step should move you forward slightly.

Stand tall with your legs straight and arms hanging at your sides. Lift up one knee and externally rotate that leg so your inner thigh is pointing up. Grab the leg with both hands and cradle it higher to stretch out the glutes. Slowly lower to repeat on the opposite side to continue moving forward.

Stand tall, holding onto a chair or wall for balance if necessary (not pictured). Keep your feet hip-width apart, your back straight and your feet parallel. Reach back and grab your left foot in your left hand, keeping your thighs lined up next to each other and left leg in line with the hip. Breathe deeply and hold for 30 seconds. Repeat on opposite side.

Stand with your feet together and hands at your waist. Take a big step forward and bend your legs to form 90 degree angles. Once in your lunge, try a few pulses. Then, straighten your legs back up and repeat, alternating sides.
